\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=135905\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:487:\"<p>Do you want to learn how to use the WordPress FAQ block to boost your SEO? WordPress FAQ blocks can increase your website traffic and click-through rates. They can even help you beat your competitors. In this tutorial, you&#8217;ll learn&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/\">How to Use a WordPress FAQ Block to Boost SEO and Get More Traffic</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Sherrie Gossett\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32242:\"<p>Do you want to learn how to use the WordPress FAQ block to boost your SEO?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress FAQ blocks can increase your website traffic and click-through rates. They can even help you beat your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial, you&#8217;ll learn how to optimize WordPress FAQ blocks and use them strategically to drive real results.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-3 wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-use-wordpress-faq-blocks\">Why Use a WordPress FAQ Block?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo\">How to Use a WordPress FAQ Block to Boost SEO</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-1-install-and-activate-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Install and Activate the All in One SEO (AIOSEO) Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-2-add-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-a-post\">Step 2: Learn How to Add an FAQ Block in WordPress</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-3-optional-choose-faq-design-and-display-options\">Step 3 (Optional): Choose FAQ Design and Display Options</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-4-review-googles-guidelines-for-faqs\">Step 4: Review Google’s Guidelines for FAQs</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-faq-content-tips\">FAQ Content Tips</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-faq-pages-and-sections\">FAQs: Where to Put Them?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-answer-faqs-well\">How to Answer FAQs Well</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-find-faqs-to-answer\">How to Come Up With FAQs to Answer</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-use-faq-blocks-to-supercharge-your-traffic\">How to Use FAQ Blocks to Supercharge Your Traffic</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-use-faqs-to-steal-your-competitors-traffic\">Use FAQs to &#8216;Steal&#8217; Your Competitor’s Traffic</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-be-objective-and-accurate\">Build Trust: Be Objective and Accurate</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-aim-to-rank-in-people-also-ask-boxes\">Aim to Appear in the &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; Boxes</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-are-people-also-ask-boxes\">What are &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; Boxes?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-create-faqs\">Steps to Get Your FAQs in PAA Boxes</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-do-faqs-need-schema-markup-to-land-in-paa-boxes\">Do FAQs Need Schema Markup to Land in PAA Boxes?</a></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-have-more-questions-about-wordpress-faq-blocks\">Have More Questions About the WordPress FAQ Block?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-an-faq-rich-snippet\">What is an FAQ rich snippet?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-do-i-move-my-wordpress-faq-block\">How Do I Move my WordPress FAQ Block?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-the-best-faq-plugin-for-wordpress\">What is the best FAQ plugin for WordPress?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-do-i-add-faqs-in-wordpress-without-a-plugin\">How do I add FAQs in WordPress without a plugin?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-can-i-add-custom-schema-markup-to-the-aioseo-plugin\">Can I add custom FAQ Schema markup to the AIOSEO plugin?</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-whats-next\">What’s Next?</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-why-use-wordpress-faq-blocks\">Why Use a WordPress FAQ Block?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Using FAQ blocks in WordPress is a proven way to <strong>increase traffic and CTRs</strong> (click-through rates).</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Using a plugin like AIOSEO is an easy way to optimize your Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) for search engines.</li><li>The plugin adds code called &#8220;FAQ Schema markup.&#8221;&nbsp;</li><li>Now your FAQs can appear in search engine results.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example using the search term &#8220;things to do in cancun&#8221;.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"469\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-1024x469.jpg\" alt=\"faq serp example\" class=\"wp-image-135912\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-1024x469.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-300x137.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-768x352.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-600x275.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-131x60.jpg 131w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example-196x90.jpg 196w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/faq-serp-example.jpg 1386w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>See how the Trip Advisor article stands out because it includes those two FAQs?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But it gets better. You can even include<em> links</em> in your FAQs. Take a look at what happens when we click on one of the FAQs in the example: It expands to reveal the answer, which contains 6 links.<br><br>So, this one search result provides 7 links for a single article.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"700\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-1024x700.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135914\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-1024x700.jpg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-300x205.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-768x525.jpg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-600x410.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-88x60.jpg 88w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example-132x90.jpg 132w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/expanded-faq-serp-example.jpg 1261w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to unlock these kind of results with WordPress FAQ blocks?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get started.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo\">How to Use a WordPress FAQ Block to Boost SEO</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-1-install-and-activate-the-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-plugin\">Step 1: Install and Activate the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All in One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>First, head over to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"\">AIOSEO</a> to get their SEO plugin.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135917\" width=\"706\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-1024x485.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-768x364.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-600x284.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-127x60.png 127w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage-190x90.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-homepage.png 1260w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is an easy-to-use WordPress plugin popular with small businesses and bloggers. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Right now, more than 3 million WordPress site owners are using AIOSEO. And a big majority of reviewers have given it a 5-star rating on WordPress.org.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the best features of this plugin is the AIOSEO FAQ block. This block will add the SEO code that your FAQs need.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After downloading the plugin from AIOSEO, open your WordPress editor and go to <strong>Plugins » Add New</strong>. Then upload the zip file of the plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Have questions? Follow the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installation-instructions-for-wordpress-com-users/\" title=\"\">instructions here</a> to install and activate it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-2-add-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-a-post\">Step 2: Learn How to Add an FAQ Block in WordPress</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you’ve installed and activated the AIOSEO plugin, you’re ready to create some FAQs.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Open your WordPress block editor (also called the Gutenberg editor).</li><li>On a post or page, click the “add block” icon (the black plus sign).&nbsp;</li><li>In the search field of the pop-up window, type in &#8220;AIOSEO.&#8221; The <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong> option will appear alongside other helpful AIOSEO blocks. Click on&nbsp;<strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"550\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-1024x550.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135923\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-1024x550.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-300x161.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-768x412.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-600x322.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-112x60.png 112w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block-168x90.png 168w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-gutenberg-block.png 1440w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An FAQ block will appear on your page with two prompts:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Write a question . . .&nbsp;</li><li>Write an answer . . .&nbsp;</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"879\" height=\"327\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135925\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts.png 879w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-300x112.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-768x286.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-600x223.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-161x60.png 161w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-faq-block-prompts-242x90.png 242w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Go ahead and type in your FAQ question and your answer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then, repeat the process to add another FAQ to your page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That was easy, wasn’t it?</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-3-optional-choose-faq-design-and-display-options\">Step 3 (Optional): Choose FAQ Design and Display Options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong> block offers several design and display options.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To view these options, place your cursor anywhere in an FAQ block on your post or page.&nbsp;The options will now display under <strong>Block</strong> in the right-hand sidebar menu.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Scroll down that right-hand column to see all the options:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"673\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-1024x673.png\" alt=\"aioseo wordpress faq block design options\" class=\"wp-image-136277\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-1024x673.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-300x197.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-768x505.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options-600x395.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-design-options.png 1326w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The options include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Title wrapper</strong>: Choose which heading tag you want to use for the FAQ questions, such as h2, h3, h4.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Visibility</strong>: By default, this is set to “Display Block.” This toggle gives you the option to hide the FAQ block from the front end of your site. That means that visitors will no longer be able to see the FAQ. Search engines will continue to see it because AIOSEO will still output the schema markup.</li><li><strong>Color</strong>: You can alter your FAQ text color or add a background color.</li><li><strong>Dimensions</strong>: You can use this to create more space around your FAQ content or to alter the margin size.</li><li><strong>Typography</strong>: Here you can alter the font size and line height.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>As you scroll down the right-hand navigation, you’ll see some <strong>Advanced</strong> options too:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>HTML anchor</strong>: This is an easy way to create an HTML anchor link. You can use the URL to link to a specific area of your FAQ.</li><li><strong>Additional CSS class(es): </strong>Here&#8217;s where you would paste CSS code to customize your FAQ&#8217;s appearance.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"620\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-1024x620.png\" alt=\"aioseo advanced faq block options\" class=\"wp-image-136276\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-1024x620.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-300x182.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-768x465.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options-600x363.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/aioseo-wordpress-faq-block-advanced-options.png 1430w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-4-review-googles-guidelines-for-faqs\">Step 4: Review Google’s Guidelines for FAQs</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We mentioned earlier that the <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong> block adds FAQ Schema markup to FAQs. This markup is a type of code that search engines need to identify FAQ content so they can display it in a special way.<br><br>It’s worth noting that Google has some guidelines for FAQ content.<br><br>For example, your FAQs should:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Include one single answer.</li><li>Have more than one question-and-answer pair. (Otherwise you&#8217;d use a different Schema markup.)</li><li>Not have an option for site visitors to submit their own answers to your question.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can read Google’s guidelines <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/appearance/structured-data/faqpage#guidelines\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Okay! Now you know how to add FAQ blocks in WordPress and optimize them for search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s talk about some content factors that can put you ahead of the game.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-faq-content-tips\">FAQ Content Tips</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep these tips and ideas in mind when planning your FAQs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-faq-pages-and-sections\">FAQs: Where to Put Them?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can create one or more FAQ pages on your site. These are resource pages that have nothing but FAQs on them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a popular option with businesses. For example, software companies often have one or more FAQ pages in the customer support area of their website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, some sites include a navigation (or sub-navigation) item labeled “FAQ.” This can improve user experience by helping site visitors find your FAQ.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also publish FAQs on pages that feature other content. For example, you can add FAQs to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Product pages</li><li>Blog posts&nbsp;</li><li>Event pages</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-how-to-answer-faqs-well\">How to Answer FAQs Well</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your answers need to be well-written if they’re going to rank. That&#8217;s because content quality is a big ranking factor.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Follow these principles and you’ll be creating quality FAQs in no time:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Be clear and use simple language</li><li>Be concise</li><li>Don’t change the subject</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>That last bit is important. We&#8217;ve all known that person who goes on and on when you ask them a simple question.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don&#8217;t be that person.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure to answer the question in the first sentence. After the first sentence, add details if they&#8217;re relevant to the question.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your readers will thank you!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-how-to-find-faqs-to-answer\">How to Come Up With FAQs to Answer</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You already know many of the questions site visitors have about your content or products.<br><br>Here are some ways to discover more FAQs to answer:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Social media</strong>: check your social media accounts for questions left by visitors.</li><li><strong>Reviews</strong>: Check online reviews for questions or customer pain points.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Blog post comments</strong>: Scan these to discover questions that are common.</li><li><strong>Support and sales teams</strong>: Meet with your team to discover repeat questions.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s kick things up a notch. Ready?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;re going to learn how to create FAQs that get you ranking higher in search results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-use-faq-blocks-to-supercharge-your-traffic\">How to Use FAQ Blocks to Supercharge Your Traffic</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to unlock the full power of FAQs, it’s not enough to optimize them for SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some insider tactics that the best (and most expensive!) content marketers use.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-use-faqs-to-steal-your-competitors-traffic\">Use FAQs to &#8216;Steal&#8217; Your Competitor’s Traffic</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know you can use FAQs to get traffic and sales from your competitors&#8217; prospects?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You do this by answering questions searchers are asking about those competitors. These questions can be about hours, prices, guarantees, refunds, services, products, features, and so on.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s look at an example of how this works.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine that DocuSign is a competitor of yours. You want to see what ranks on page 1 for the search term (keyword)&nbsp;“does DocuSign charge per user?” (That&#8217;s a question a prospect might have before purchasing DocuSign.)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>First, open up the Chrome browser in Incognito mode. (If you&#8217;re using a different browser, use their version of privacy/incognito mode.)&nbsp;</li><li>Search for&nbsp;“does DocuSign charge per user?”&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Page 1 of search engine result pages (SERPs) for that keyword shows us something interesting.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SignNow, which is a competitor to DocuSign, has answered this FAQ. Because they&#8217;ve answered it well, it’s currently ranking on page 1 of search results for that keyword.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"572\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-1024x572.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135953\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-1024x572.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-300x168.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-768x429.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-600x335.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-107x60.png 107w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example-161x90.png 161w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/signnow-faq-serp-example.png 1137w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So now, people searching for details on DocuSign&#8217;s pricing can find out about SignNow. And when they click through to SignNow, they’ll see it’s cheaper. Clever!</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-be-objective-and-accurate\">Build Trust: Be Objective and Accurate</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>When answering FAQs on your competitors, it’s important to be accurate. You can even say good things about their product where warranted.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The more you sound like a trustworthy third party in your competitor FAQs, the more likely your answers will rank well. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please note that this doesn&#8217;t mean you are trying to trick Google. Search engines know the source of any given FAQ. The goal here is to meet Google&#8217;s standards for quality. Quality is always a huge ranking factor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t forget to say why your product might be a better alternative. For example, if you offer a free feature that your competitor charges for, say so.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You don’t always need to highlight your benefits in the FAQ answer itself though. Use your judgement.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember, you’re using the FAQ about your competitor to get click-throughs to your website. Once the visitors are on your web page, they can read more about how your products compare.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Tip: Include one or more internal links in the answers where relevant or practical. But don’t force a link into an answer if you have no good options for one.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-aim-to-rank-in-people-also-ask-boxes\">Aim to Appear in the &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; Boxes</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let&#8217;s look at how you can get your FAQs to land in People Also Ask boxes.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-what-are-people-also-ask-boxes\">What are &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; Boxes?</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Google often (but not always) displays a section on page 1 of search results called “People Also Ask&#8221; (PAA). These are common questions people have about the related search term.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As such, they reveal important information about search intent.<br><br>To see an example of PAA let&#8217;s open Chrome Incognito. Type in the same search term as before (“does DocuSign charge per user?”).<br><br>Now scroll down a bit to find the “People Also Ask” questions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-1024x485.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135957\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-1024x485.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-768x364.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-600x284.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-127x60.png 127w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example-190x90.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/people-also-ask-example.png 1229w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you click on each question, its answer will appear. After clicking on a question, additional &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; questions will appear at the bottom of the box.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s look at the first PAA question: &#8220;How much does it cost to add a user to DocuSign?&#8221; </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking on the question reveals it&#8217;s been answered by PandaDoc, another DocuSign competitor!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"977\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-135961\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1.png 977w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-300x246.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-768x629.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-600x491.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-73x60.png 73w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/ppa-competitor-faq-example-1-110x90.png 110w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-how-to-create-faqs\">Steps to Get Your FAQs in PAA Boxes</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To boost the chances that some of your FAQs will appear in a PAA box, we recommend taking these steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>For each article you write, identify the main topic first. In SEO, this is called a keyword, a search term, or a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/using-the-focus-keyphrase-to-analyze-your-content/\" title=\"Using the Focus Keyphrase to Analyze Your Content\">focus keyphrase</a>. (Follow <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-properly-use-focus-keyphrase-in-wordpress-beginners-guide/\" title=\"\">these easy instructions</a>.) This is good SEO practice for every article. But it&#8217;s also going to help you find relevant PAA to answer. This is because PAA questions appear in relation to a search term.</li><li>For each page or post you create, search in Chrome Incognito for your article&#8217;s main keyword.</li><li>Explore the People Also Ask questions that appear.&nbsp;</li><li>Choose some PAA questions to answer in your article. (Not all PAA questions will be relevant to your keyword. Use your judgment when choosing which ones to answer.)&nbsp;</li><li>Add your FAQs to your page.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-do-faqs-need-schema-markup-to-land-in-paa-boxes\">Do FAQs Need Schema Markup to Land in PAA Boxes?</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>At this point, we want share some nuanced information. Your FAQs don&#8217;t need FAQ Schema markup applied to them in order to be selected by Google to appear in a PAA box.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The quality of your answer, and the nature of the competition, are the two biggest ranking factors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, we recommend you always optimize your FAQs with Schema markup so that you run a higher chance of getting your FAQs displayed, along with your title and description, in regular search results. (See the &#8220;things to do in cancun&#8221; example at the beginning of this article.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Great, we&#8217;ve covered some ideas for FAQ content and some strategic moves that can make a significant difference in your ranking.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember: to rank for FAQs, be concise and clear in your answers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To the degree that you help the reader, Google, Bing, Yandex, and other search engines will reward you.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-have-more-questions-about-wordpress-faq-blocks\">Have More Questions About the WordPress FAQ Block?</h2>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-what-is-an-faq-rich-snippet\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">What is an FAQ rich snippet? </h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>An FAQ rich snippet (or &#8220;FAQ rich result&#8221;) refers to the way Google displays some FAQs in search results. To appear as a &#8220;rich snippet,&#8221; an FAQ must have FAQ schema markup added to it. In search results, FAQ rich snippets appear beneath an article&#8217;s title and description. They appear in accordion format (clicking on a question reveals the answer). FAQ rich snippets can include links in the answer area.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-how-do-i-move-my-wordpress-faq-block\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">How Do I Move my WordPress FAQ Block?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>To move your WordPress FAQ block, do the following: Place your cursor inside the FAQ block. Then select the 6-dot “Drag“ icon to drag and drop the block where you want it. Or click the “Move up” or “Move down” arrow to move the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>(If you don’t have any content below the FAQ, then the “Move down” arrow will appear grayed out.)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"941\" height=\"283\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-136316\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block.png 941w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-300x90.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-768x231.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-600x180.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-190x57.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/move-wordpress-faq-block-299x90.png 299w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-what-is-the-best-faq-plugin-for-wordpress\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">What is the best FAQ plugin for WordPress?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>The <a href=\"http://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-faq-plugins/\" title=\"\">best WordPress FAQ plugins</a> optimize your content for SEO. And they provide design options. Here are some recommendations:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>All in One SEO (AIOSEO) plugin</li><li>FAQ by 10Web</li><li>Heroic WordPress FAQ Plugin (allows video embeds in answer sections)</li><li>Tribulant WordPress FAQ Plugin</li><li>Quick and Easy FAQs</li><li>Ultimate FAQ</li><li>Helpie FAQ (Helpie FAQ also includes WooCommerce and Elementor integrations)</li></ul>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-how-do-i-add-faqs-in-wordpress-without-a-plugin\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">How do I add FAQs in WordPress without a plugin?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>To create an FAQ section in WordPress without using a plugin:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>First, navigate to the page or post in question.</li><li>Use an h2, h3, or h4 heading for your questions.</li><li>Add a paragraph block below each question for the answer.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>But remember, using a WordPress FAQ block plugin will optimize your FAQ for SEO. This ensures that your FAQs can display as rich snippets in search results. SEO-optimized FAQs are an important part of growing your site traffic.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div data-schema-only=\"false\" class=\"wp-block-aioseo-faq\" id=\"aioseo-can-i-add-custom-schema-markup-to-the-aioseo-plugin\"><h3 class=\"aioseo-faq-block-question\">Can I add custom FAQ Schema markup to the AIOSEO plugin?</h3><div class=\"aioseo-faq-block-answer\">\n<p>Yes, you can add custom FAQ Schema markup to the AIOSEO plugin. For example, you could add the property <strong>reviewedBy</strong> if you use a subject matter expert to fact-check your authors’ FAQs. Follow these simple <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/creating-custom-schema-markup-with-all-in-one-seo/\">instructions</a> for adding your Schema markup in JSON-LD. You can <a href=\"http://​​​​​​​https://aioseo.com/docs/testing-your-schema-in-all-in-one-seo/\" title=\"validate your code\">validate your code</a> by clicking a button. And you can save the custom Schema as a template.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-whats-next\">What’s Next?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimized FAQ blocks can drive traffic to your site and improve your rankings.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And you’ve seen how you can use them to grab market share from competitors.<br><br>We hope this article has helped you learn how to use FAQ blocks to boost SEO and get more traffic. Next, check out our tips on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-boost-your-small-business-seo/\">boosting SEO without expert help</a>. And explore some easy ways to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/\">increase your click-through rates</a> (CTRs.)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/\">How to Use a WordPress FAQ Block to Boost SEO and Get More Traffic</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-wordpress-faq-block-to-boost-seo-and-get-more-traffic/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"How to Add Shipping Information to Google Search Snippets Using WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:210:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-shipping-information-to-google-search-snippets-using-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-shipping-information-to-google-search-snippets-using-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:102:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-shipping-information-to-google-search-snippets-using-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 21 Nov 2022 16:22:59 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"adding shipping information to search snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"Google Merchant Center\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"product rich snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=136269\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:518:\"<p>Would you like to know how to add shipping information to Google search snippets using WordPress? Having your shipping information displayed on search engine results pages (SERPs) is a powerful way to boost conversion rates and drive sales.&#160; In this&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-shipping-information-to-google-search-snippets-using-wordpress/\">How to Add Shipping Information to Google Search Snippets Using WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15083:\"<p>Would you like to know how to add shipping information to Google search snippets using WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Having your shipping information displayed on search engine results pages (SERPs) is a powerful way to boost conversion rates and drive sales.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to add shipping information to your product rich snippets using WordPress. This will help you display shipping details in your search snippets.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-4 wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-are-product-rich-snippets\">What are Product Rich Snippets?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-adding-shipping-information-to-product-rich-snippets-is-important\">Why Adding Shipping Information to Product Rich Snippets is Important</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-add-shipping-information-to-your-search-snippets-using-wordpress\">How to Add Shipping Information to Your Search Snippets Using WordPress</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-1-install-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Step 1: Install All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-2-add-product-schema\">Step 2: Add Product Schema</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-step-3-edit-product-schema-to-add-shipping-information\">Step 3: Edit Product Schema to Add Shipping Information</a></li></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-are-product-rich-snippets\">What are Product Rich Snippets?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-rich-snippets-to-wordpress/\">Rich snippets</a> are the interactive results Google displays in search.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"237\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-rich-snippet-example.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to add shipping information to Google search snippets results in enhanced rich snippets.\" class=\"wp-image-136297\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-rich-snippet-example.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-rich-snippet-example-300x102.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-rich-snippet-example-600x203.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These include additional information, such as product images, star ratings, reviews, prices, etc. The purpose of rich snippets is to answer users’ questions immediately by showing as much information as possible straight from the search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Product rich snippets, therefore, are snippets that specifically give users more information about your product right on SERPs. Another invaluable piece of information you can add to your product rich snippets is shipping details. We’ll show you how to do that in a moment.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more detailed information about product rich snippets and how to add them in WordPress, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-product-rich-snippets-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add Product Rich Snippets in WordPress (The Easiest Way)\">check out this easy-to-follow guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-theme-notice-box\" role=\"alert\">\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Interactive rich snippets are generated by Schema markup. Schema markup is code that works in the background to give search engines more information about your page, so they output rich snippets.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-why-adding-shipping-information-to-product-rich-snippets-is-important\">Why Adding Shipping Information to Product Rich Snippets is Important</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding shipping information to your search snippets greatly impacts your business&#8217;s growth. Some reasons for this include the following:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Increases conversions</strong>: Displaying shipping information on your product snippets encourages more clickthrough rates (CTRs) as shoppers know the product will reach them.</li><li><strong>Reduces cart abandonment:</strong> <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/cart-abandonment-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\">55% of shoppers abandon carts</a> because of surprise costs, like shipping, at checkout. Displaying shipping information on SERPs is an excellent way to combat cart abandonment.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Increases your average order value (AOV)</strong>: Clear shipping information encourages shoppers to add more products to their cart. This results in increased AOV.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, shipping plays a huge role in ecommerce conversion rate optimization, helping you drive more sales. That’s why displaying it on SERPs is something you should strongly consider doing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-add-shipping-information-to-your-search-snippets-using-wordpress\">How to Add Shipping Information to Your Search Snippets Using WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to add shipping information to your search snippets?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an easy step-by-step guide to help you do just that.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-1-install-all-in-one-seo-aioseo\">Step 1: Install All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to adding shipping information to your search snippets is to install and activate <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/adding-seo-keywords-aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is a powerful tool that can help you add shipping information to Google search snippets.\" class=\"wp-image-95222\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/adding-seo-keywords-aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/adding-seo-keywords-aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/adding-seo-keywords-aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a> is a powerful yet easy-to-use WordPress SEO plugin that has been downloaded over 100 million times. Savvy website owners and marketers trust the plugin to help boost their search rankings and drive relevant site traffic. This is because AIOSEO has many <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\" title=\"Features\">powerful features and modules</a> designed to help you optimize your website for search engines and users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most loved features in AIOSEO is the next-gen Schema Generator.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a revolutionary module that makes it easy to add any type of schema markup to your posts and pages. Ecommerce merchants especially love this feature as it makes it easy to add product schema to your post and pages. AIOSEO’s Product schema module also supports Google’s Merchant Center listing schema, a feature that enables you to generate interactive snippets on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most importantly, the Product schema module allows you to add shipping information to your search snippets.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on how to install AIOSEO, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-2-add-product-schema\">Step 2: Add Product Schema</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve installed and activated AIOSEO, the next step to adding shipping information to your search snippets is to add product schema to your page or post. To do that, you must first open the page in editor mode.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, scroll down to the <strong>AIOSEO Settings » Schema</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"399\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/product-rich-schema-01-1.png\" alt=\"To add shipping information to Google search snippets, you must first add Product schema to your page or post.\" class=\"wp-image-137022\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/product-rich-schema-01-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/product-rich-schema-01-1-300x171.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/product-rich-schema-01-1-600x341.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If the schema type on that page is not set to <strong>Product</strong>, click on the <strong>Generate Schema</strong> button. Doing so will open up our <strong>Schema Catalog, </strong>a modal from which you can select and add product schema markup.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"403\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/product-rich-schema-product-option-1.png\" alt=\"Open the Schema Generator and select the Product option from the Schema Catalog.\" class=\"wp-image-133541\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/product-rich-schema-product-option-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/product-rich-schema-product-option-1-300x173.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/product-rich-schema-product-option-1-600x345.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-step-3-edit-product-schema-to-add-shipping-information\">Step 3: Edit Product Schema to Add Shipping Information</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The next step to adding shipping information to your search snippets is to fill in (or edit) your product information.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, click the edit button as shown below:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"407\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-google-merchant-center-schema-01.png\" alt=\"Click the &quot;Edit&quot; icon to edit your Product schema information.\" class=\"wp-image-137025\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-google-merchant-center-schema-01.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-google-merchant-center-schema-01-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-google-merchant-center-schema-01-600x348.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open a modal with fields for all the relevant product details needed to generate product schema.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add your shipping information, scroll down until you find the <strong>Shipping Destinations</strong> section.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"537\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-shipping-destinations-1.png\" alt=\"To add your shipping information, scroll down until you find the Shipping Destinations section. \" class=\"wp-image-137026\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-shipping-destinations-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-shipping-destinations-1-300x229.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-shipping-destinations-1-600x459.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Fill in all the fields to add information about a shipping destination you support:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Country</li><li>States</li><li>Postal Code</li><li>Price</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO will generate schema markup using this information, which will be output in the form of rich snippets on SERPs. Here’s an example below:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"303\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-snippet-example.png\" alt=\"Example of shipping information in product rich snippets.\" class=\"wp-image-137027\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-snippet-example.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-snippet-example-300x130.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-snippet-example-600x260.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Notice the “Free 6-10 day delivery” in the snippet. Shipping information like this makes a huge difference in increasing your CTR.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add other destinations by clicking on the <strong>Add Another Shipping Destination</strong> link.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"411\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-add-destination-1.png\" alt=\"You can add another shipping destination by clicking on the &quot; Add Another Shipping Destination&quot; link.\" class=\"wp-image-137030\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-add-destination-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-add-destination-1-300x176.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/how-to-add-shipping-information-add-destination-1-600x351.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re a WooCommerce user, then you’ll be glad to know AIOSEO supports WooCommerce shipping out of the box! This means fewer changes you need to make.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve added all the shipping destinations you support, click the <strong>Update Schema</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that’s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve added shipping information to your search snippets using WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you learn how to add shipping information to your product search snippets using WordPress.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to learn more SEO tips?&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out our other articles, including our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-schema-markup-to-boost-your-seo/\" title=\"How to Use Schema Markup to Boost Your SEO\">boosting your SEO using schema markup</a> and our tutorial on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-emojis-to-your-seo-titles-and-meta-descriptions/\" title=\"How to Add Emojis to Your SEO Titles and Meta Descriptions\">adding emojis to your search snippets</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-shipping-information-to-google-search-snippets-using-wordpress/\">How to Add Shipping Information to Google Search Snippets Using WordPress</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-shipping-information-to-google-searc